rldregora.ancient.the_encounter.title=The Encounter
rldregora.ancient.the_encounter.author=Navigational Officer
rldregora.ancient.the_encounter.lore=A old book, signed by the Dregorian Voyager navigational officer
rldregora.ancient.the_encounter.page.1=After spending over a thousand years in space we returned to Earth knowing that since the time of departure approximately 1100 years had passed. Expecting to be welcomed by a thousand voices, we were met with silence.\n\n 
rldregora.ancient.the_encounter.page.2=For a long time we came up with all manner of theories but none had prepared us for what we saw once in range of Earth: A desolate Mars-like planet with wide deserts and no communications whatsoever. What happened to the Earth?

rldregora.ancient.logbook.title=Logbook
rldregora.ancient.logbook.author=Ecologist
rldregora.ancient.logbook.lore=An old book signed by a Dregorian Ecologist
rldregora.ancient.logbook.page.1=After scanning the world, a viable spot revealed itself containing a small ocean, or perhaps a big lake. The board gathered and voted. The decision to start over on this planet was unanimous and preparations began.
rldregora.ancient.logbook.page.2=Meanwhile, our scientists shocked us by announcing the actual date, accounting for time dilation due to relativity. It's now the year 6156 (give or take a couple months), close to 4000 years later! Much longer than we initially thought.\n\n 
rldregora.ancient.logbook.page.3=But what happened? As an ecologist, I assure you even a hundred thousand years couldn't explain the strange creatures roaming the planet. Oddly, I note this strange new life seems diminished wherever there is water...

rldregora.ancient.soldiers_diary.title=Soldier's Diary
rldregora.ancient.soldiers_diary.author=Soldier
rldregora.ancient.soldiers_diary.lore=An old book signed by a Dregorian Soldier
rldregora.ancient.soldiers_diary.page.1=Year 6236, 80 years after the arrival of the Dregorian Voyager and we have settled in a valley now known as Dregora. There are no traces of our green Earth reclaiming the Endlands beyond Dregora yet, but we keep our hopes up.
rldregora.ancient.soldiers_diary.page.2=All things considered, we are grateful for this small pearl of life. Beyond the edge of Dregora the biggest monsters roam in large numbers while they pop up here only sparingly. If only we still had the Dregorian Voyager slaying these would have been trivial. 

rldregora.ancient.captains_log.title=Captain's Log
rldregora.ancient.captains_log.author=Dregorian Captain
rldregora.ancient.captains_log.lore=An old book signed by the captain of the Dregorian Voyager
rldregora.ancient.captains_log.page.1=It is year 2300 or 8537 according to the ancient books from the Great Library. The deck boards of my ship, the Dregorian Voyager, creak under my feet as we ready to hoist the sail.
rldregora.ancient.captains_log.page.2=Today is Dregorian Founder's Day, which we celebrate in honor of the arrival. This time around it was up to me to carry on the ancient knowledge as part of our tradition.
rldregora.ancient.captains_log.page.3=I never took an interest in the weird structures in the wastelands, however reading the ancient books piqued my curiosity. The books told me they were once huge villages equal or greater than the size of kingdoms with millions of people living in
rldregora.ancient.captains_log.page.4=them with flying machines and more. It's hard to believe we once lived in such a place before the monsters arrived. It makes me question what kind of secrets and treasures still remain hidden in the lands beyond.

rldregora.ancient.adventurers_log.title=Adventurer's Log
rldregora.ancient.adventurers_log.author=Khaldir Murdok
rldregora.ancient.adventurers_log.lore=A lost note from Khaldir's Log.
rldregora.ancient.adventurers_log.page.1=It is now several months since I made the decision to go on a journey to the lands beyond, also known as the Endlands. So far on my journey I've found several logbooks in ancient structures. Some of these structures are taken by the
rldregora.ancient.adventurers_log.page.2=corrupt monsters from ancient times. It's strange to find so many logbooks within these ruins - maybe they're being collected by the evil entities guarding those places.

rldregora.ancient.totem_luck.name=Totem of §l§6Legendary§r Luck
rldregora.ancient.totem_luck.lore=Noice!
#,LocName:\"rldregora.ancient.totem_luck.name\",LocLore:[\"rldregora.ancient.totem_luck.lore\"]

##################################################################
# lore/bunker.json
##################################################################
rldregora.bunker.wastelanders_guide.title=The Wastelanders Guide
rldregora.bunker.wastelanders_guide.author=Wastelanders Council
rldregora.bunker.wastelanders_guide.lore=This book describes the task of the Wastelander within this settlement.
rldregora.bunker.wastelanders_guide.page.1=The tasks of the Wastelanders is as dangerous as it is vital for the survival of the shelter given to us by those who prospered before.\n\nBeyond the doors lay many dangers but our future as well and those brave enough
rldregora.bunker.wastelanders_guide.page.2=will be selected to travel from here to villages, outposts and shelters spread throughout the wastelands in search of knowledge, news, food and valuables which may raise our standards of living.\n\nThe most important rules for traveling to
rldregora.bunker.wastelanders_guide.page.3=and from these settlements are to\n\n1. Security - always remain alert of your surroundings.\n\n2. Avoid - Avoid any life-beings. Especially other traveling villagers! They may be imposters.
rldregora.bunker.wastelanders_guide.page.4=3. Fast - be as fast as you can be unless it becomes dark.\n\n4. Encamp - never travel at night! Always make a secure encampment.\n\nThese 4 points make up the initialism S.A.F.E.

rldregora.bunker.evacuation_plan.title=Evacuation Plan
rldregora.bunker.evacuation_plan.author=United World
rldregora.bunker.evacuation_plan.lore=These are copies of copies and preserve a ancient directive.
rldregora.bunker.evacuation_plan.page.1=--- EVACUATION ---\n\nFollow the supplied GPS coordinates to your closest shelter though the UW-APP where you will need to abandon your vehicle and follow the directions of military personel.
rldregora.bunker.evacuation_plan.page.2=Upon arrival you will go down a set of stairs until you arrive at the tunnel at which you'll need to walk a few kilometers dependent on your designated shelter included in your UW-APP.\n\nProceeding calmly and listening to the local military personel is
rldregora.bunker.evacuation_plan.page.3=of great importance.\n\nAt your designated shelter you will go through the blast doors which will close at the following time:\n\nWeekday: Monday\nDate: 26/04/2116

rldregora.bunker.the_abyss.title=The Abyss
rldregora.bunker.the_abyss.author=Unknown
rldregora.bunker.the_abyss.lore=This book warns for a place one should avoid at all cost.
rldregora.bunker.the_abyss.page.1=Beyond the edge of the wastelands lay the realms of no return in which few brave, some desperate but all foolish go in search of unclaimed treasure or glory.\n\nThose lands shrouded in heavy fog and silent whispers should not
rldregora.bunker.the_abyss.page.2=be taken at face value as though dread may fill your mind upon staring into the void if one enters a worse fate awaits.\n\nIt is rumored that even till this day those who venture close can hear the screams of their predecessors.

rldregora.bunker.tutors_guide.title=The Tutors Guide
rldregora.bunker.tutors_guide.author=Wastelanders Council
rldregora.bunker.tutors_guide.lore=This book describes the task of the tutor within this settlement.
rldregora.bunker.tutors_guide.page.1=The tutors of this settlement fill the role of passing on gained knowledge through books or the words of the wastelanders.\n\nImportant for these tutors is to teach about the dangers of spreading knowledge\n\n 
rldregora.bunker.tutors_guide.page.2=gained to outside trusted circles for then raiders may come and unspeakable things ensue.\n\nThe knowledge in particular often centers around artifacts and ancient documents which we should learn about but
rldregora.bunker.tutors_guide.page.3=never write down or hold in our possession for too long.\n\nThe only exception to these rules is made for the artifacts traded by the outposts for reasons debatable.

rldregora.bunker.reclaimation_day.title=Reclaimation Day
rldregora.bunker.reclaimation_day.author=Unknown
rldregora.bunker.reclaimation_day.lore=A copy of a copy of a old book, most pages fell out but a small note remained.
rldregora.bunker.reclaimation_day.page.1=Reclaimation day speech.\n\nToday marks our Reclaimation day for we have cleaned the corruption out of our newfound home and shall sleep sound for the doors are strong.\n\nNow we shall fix what is broken and farm what lands we have in peace.
rldregora.bunker.reclaimation_day.page.2=We've traveled under many days and survived many a nights full of terror and doom.\n\nNow it is our time to be happy if not for our sakes then for those who we lost on our way to this utopia amids the waste.\n\n19/11/6236 Saturday

##################################################################
# lore/dungeonone.json
##################################################################
rldregora.dungeonone.explorers_log.title=Explorer's Log
rldregora.dungeonone.explorers_log.author=Jude Koorn
rldregora.dungeonone.explorers_log.lore=A lost note from Jude Koorn's Log.
rldregora.dungeonone.explorers_log.page.1=It has been days since my companions and I entered the depths of this dungeon to find ourselves trapped soon after. We just ate our last portion of food and the exit is guarded by foul beasts. Although, exploring other relatively safe parts of
rldregora.dungeonone.explorers_log.page.2=the dungeon made us wonder, even if we manage to defeat the beasts, will we find the exit? There is only one way to know, and I hope this won't be my last entry. May we be blessed by those who call themselves the RedClan in our attempt to escape.\n 

rldregora.dungeonone.historians_log.title=Historian's Log
rldregora.dungeonone.historians_log.author=Mark Dragor
rldregora.dungeonone.historians_log.lore=A lost note from Mark Dragor's Log.
rldregora.dungeonone.historians_log.page.1=It's widely known that the Corrupted Ancients have no way of communicating with one another, and always seem to hunger for fresh meat. However, recent discoveries within the depths of this dungeon prove otherwise. There seems to be some sort of
rldregora.dungeonone.historians_log.page.2=entity which controls it all. It makes me wonder if this is the case for all the dungeons throughout the land of Dregora. Nevertheless, we will continue our research and possibly try to communicate with this leader by luring it to the upper
rldregora.dungeonone.historians_log.page.3=layers of the dungeon. Our hopes for succeeding are high but we will need to be patient.

rldregora.dungeonone.wanderers_log.title=Wanderer's Log
rldregora.dungeonone.wanderers_log.author=Philip Austin
rldregora.dungeonone.wanderers_log.lore=A lost note from Philip Austin's Log.
rldregora.dungeonone.wanderers_log.page.1=I feel something within myself changing... What's happening? Don't tell me I'm turning into one of those, no that's not possible! How can this happen? Other worldly thoughts are filling my mind but not only.. No not only! I Feel anger,
rldregora.dungeonone.wanderers_log.page.2=sorrow and change... I like change yes. I'm hungry and craving. No! I Can't let this happen, I need to write to focus on my own being. Hahahahaha! I'm Thorin Gunthar from the depths of despair. It's over...\n\n 

rldregora.dungeonone.outlaw.title=Outlaw
rldregora.dungeonone.outlaw.author=Outlaw
rldregora.dungeonone.outlaw.lore=Notes from an Outlaw.
rldregora.dungeonone.outlaw.page.1=We live by ambushing those who manage to return from the dungeons, a place I would never visit. Great treasures can be found unknown to all of Dregora. This is how I obtained Lunae packed with the power of a thousand strings. I rarely
rldregora.dungeonone.outlaw.page.2=even write anymore. My companions say that's something for adventurers and explorers, but I found myself being inspired by those. I could've never thought I would regret what I had done, but it's too late now and I got to make a living.
rldregora.dungeonone.outlaw.page.3=So we walk and walk towards the next dungeon in wait for the returning souls. Who knows what we may encounter.

rldregora.dungeonone.dark_encounter.title=A Dark Encounter
rldregora.dungeonone.dark_encounter.author=Elithr
rldregora.dungeonone.dark_encounter.lore=Notes from Elithr.
rldregora.dungeonone.dark_encounter.page.1=Entry 1: These weird structures have been popping up lately, buried under the sand now being revealed. One appeared next to our town! Can you imagine? We only explored the entrance but were scared off by weird noises and moving shadows.
rldregora.dungeonone.dark_encounter.page.2=We have boarded the entrance to make sure whatever is in it never comes out.\n\nEntry 2: Somehow the boarding disappeared over night and people went missing... What in Dregora's name is going on? We may be better off re-burying the
rldregora.dungeonone.dark_encounter.page.3=dungeon before more people start going missing.\n\nEntry 3: We buried it with rocks, sand, and dirt... It didn't help. One night later people disappeared again and now I am left with but\n\n 
rldregora.dungeonone.dark_encounter.page.4=a handful of people moving away from the village. I lost my wife... I can't leave her so I will go and find her, whatever it takes.

rldregora.dungeonone.dark_encounter2.title=A Dark Encounter Part 2
rldregora.dungeonone.dark_encounter2.author=Elithr
rldregora.dungeonone.dark_encounter2.lore=Notes from Elithr.
rldregora.dungeonone.dark_encounter2.page.1=I lost my journal. Oh well, it just contained a couple of lines. Now I've found my wife, although in bad shape, I'm glad. Now we will have to find a way out and escape these hallways of death and terror. Monsters lurk around every corner so we will only have one shot
rldregora.dungeonone.dark_encounter2.page.2=at this. I really hope we will make it.

rldregora.dungeonone.the_origin1.title=The Origin Part 1
rldregora.dungeonone.the_origin1.author=Luthor
rldregora.dungeonone.the_origin1.lore=Luthor's research
rldregora.dungeonone.the_origin1.page.1=After extended research on the Dungeons and their inhabitants, these structures seem to have served as tombs later to be reformed by those whom we refer to as the Ancients or Corrupted. We think they're beings that were once just like us,
rldregora.dungeonone.the_origin1.page.2=or the wildlife in general, but corrupted by powers which are rumored to be caused by The Blight, a disaster that destroyed the world as we formerly knew it. These powers also caused rocks to float and magic to appear. We have yet to discover the full
rldregora.dungeonone.the_origin1.page.3=potential of these magical powers. This progresses extremely slowly as everyone is afraid of catching The Blight, which would mean becoming corrupted.\n 

rldregora.dungeonone.lost_book_thalnir.title=Lost Book of Thalnir
rldregora.dungeonone.lost_book_thalnir.author=Thalnir
rldregora.dungeonone.lost_book_thalnir.lore=Our own Enemies.
rldregora.dungeonone.lost_book_thalnir.page.1='Dregorian', an honorable title which we do not deserve. Yes we came back to grow trees, raise livestock and make a living just like our ancestors did. Not only did they do that, they devoured the livestock, cut down all trees, and ruined this planet.
rldregora.dungeonone.lost_book_thalnir.page.2=We are not much better than the myths of the corrupted. Tales travel from afar about these beings, mythical creatures you would find in historical books. This is a short telling of what I think of the current era we live in, the Era of The Blight,
rldregora.dungeonone.lost_book_thalnir.page.3=trying to resist against its foul offspring. A true battle, and at the same time something humanity needs so as not to fight each other again like we did in 'The War Which None May Forget'. Ironically, a war which has already been forgotten by most. 
rldregora.dungeonone.lost_book_thalnir.page.4=But to those who keep on living, to those of The Red Clan... May the monsters never die, as we need them to be truly human.

rldregora.dungeonone.night_falling.title=Night is Falling
rldregora.dungeonone.night_falling.author=A Farmer
rldregora.dungeonone.night_falling.lore=The Night is falling by a unknown farmer.
rldregora.dungeonone.night_falling.page.1=I am nothing but a humble farmer trapped within these hallways of death, together with my friends, townsmen, and some strangers. Yet not anymore as months passed and they turned at each other, there is no one here... or so we
rldregora.dungeonone.night_falling.page.2=think. There may be something hiding in the shadows which explains the moving walls, doors where there were no doors and vice versa. Pigs, sheep, cabbage... yes I miss my cabbage as I do not long for meat anymore, not after what I've
rldregora.dungeonone.night_falling.page.3=seen happening to what were once my friends, the townsmen, and the strangers. I am one of the few left, families are gone forever. The humanity in us is slowly fading away... What are we about to become?\n 

rldregora.dungeonone.cursed_treasure.title=Cursed Treasure
rldregora.dungeonone.cursed_treasure.author=Unknown
rldregora.dungeonone.cursed_treasure.lore=A note by a fool of a treasure hunter.
rldregora.dungeonone.cursed_treasure.page.1=Treasures hidden deep within, we found them but we also lost our way out. Day in, day out, we fight the monsters while trying to haul the loot outside, but every stairwell seems to lead to another new dungeon with even more treasures.
rldregora.dungeonone.cursed_treasure.page.2=We have a close group of adventurers so there won't be anything to stop us, especially now that we've acquired a heavenly sword from what we think was the guardian of this dungeon. There's a lot of bad tales going around but if you
rldregora.dungeonone.cursed_treasure.page.3=find yourself in here and find this letter, do not despair as that is what they want, to overmaster you. Be strong and find the light.\n 

rldregora.dungeonone.corrupted_shield.name=Corrupted Shield
rldregora.dungeonone.corrupted_shield.lore=With this shield you will deal significant more damage but at a cost...

