rldregora.frozen.unsend_letters.title=Unsent letters
rldregora.frozen.unsend_letters.author=Unknown
rldregora.frozen.unsend_letters.lore=A frozen book. The pages are unreadable but folded inside remains a letter.
rldregora.frozen.unsend_letters.page.1=Dear Peter,\n\nI know I promised to return home before Christmas but the weather does not seem to be in our favour. We fear there is a storm brewing so decided to make a detour along colder regions before we set course to our destination.
rldregora.frozen.unsend_letters.page.2=This will add a few more weeks to our voyage for which I am sorry as I know how much you look forward to Christmas. So how about in the new year we go on a hunting trip together? Perhaps if you eat well enough, get strong and listen to your mother I'll let
rldregora.frozen.unsend_letters.page.3=you handle my bow! Once I arrive at the destination I will try to look for some gifts to bring back as well. It can't be too big because the captain would notice but perhaps some little trinkets will miss his ever watchfull eye.
rldregora.frozen.unsend_letters.page.4=If you and your friends are planning to go sledding before my return please do be carefull as I fear this year's winter will be a harsh one. Also take care of your sister for me please you know how busy your mother is with the farm. 
rldregora.frozen.unsend_letters.page.5=Tell her pa loves her and is going to bring back a nice warm scarf for both her, you and my dear.\n\n\n\n\nLove,\nYour Dad

rldregora.frozen.white_death.title=White Death
rldregora.frozen.white_death.author=Unknown
rldregora.frozen.white_death.lore=A red stained frozen book of which half seems to be missing.
rldregora.frozen.white_death.page.1=Lost at the solid white sea as we hacked away at the ice in a race against time to save the ship in a battle against what seemed like a ancient monster deadset on taking us and the ship for thropies for ever to be frozen in both time and place.
rldregora.frozen.white_death.page.2=Low rumbling and growling sometimes filled the white plains around us which before moments was a calm ocean. Tormented by the idea of a hungry beast that is either the ice breaking and forming or a monster of unknown origins. Never had we heard of beasts
rldregora.frozen.white_death.page.3=roaming these particular lands but sometimes people did went missing.. Lost or something else?\n\nLoud noises broke the silence, this wasn't the famillair sound of breaking ice but something much bigger and then it appeared.
rldregora.frozen.white_death.page.4=A huge monster clad in white with razor sharp claws. One and then Two of the crew where slashed apart before everyone made it inside of the creaking ship as if the ship itself were afraid as well. And as soon as we turned around we saw a glimse of he bodies being dragged away. 

rldregora.frozen.uncanny_paradise.title=Depths of Uncanny Paradise
rldregora.frozen.uncanny_paradise.author=Unknown
rldregora.frozen.uncanny_paradise.lore=A few loose pages seem all that remains of this journal.
rldregora.frozen.uncanny_paradise.page.1=Day 577\n\nWe landed before the coast made of ice and gathered all the tools for our expedition. In the distance we could make out some mountains which we ventured towards in the hope for a forests or more lush environment.
rldregora.frozen.uncanny_paradise.page.2=It is night now, we had found a cave to shelter out the storm that formed next to the mountains. Further in seems to consist solely out of ice.
rldregora.frozen.uncanny_paradise.page.3=Day 579\n\nIt has been many hours, probably a day or maybe even two... Yes probably two days. We woke up and a few of us were missing on the night of day 577. As we investigated we found trails of a thing...
rldregora.frozen.uncanny_paradise.page.4=A beast dragging our comrades away towards the outside of the caverns. As we went back to the camp we found more trails, new ones leading towards the cave and just at that moment we heard the echo's of those who stayed behind. Screaming.. then the screams got closer,
rldregora.frozen.uncanny_paradise.page.5=next to me this thing. It ripped open jackson my pall. We ran, we all ran and by some luck we did so in the same direction. Deeper and deeper within the caves.. we ran and ran until we couldn't then we slept and not all of us woke up, just a few before we
rldregora.frozen.uncanny_paradise.page.6=heard more screams far away. Scared we descended further and further until we made it to a forest. Underground.... how odd. We heard of tales from the jungle but would never imagine underground forests here in this frozen wasteland..
rldregora.frozen.uncanny_paradise.page.7=We made a fire with the dry wood and we rested. It was a lot warmer here too.
rldregora.frozen.uncanny_paradise.page.8=Day 583\n\nI'm the only one left... There are no beasts here.. not the white ones no. It's much worse... They move fast and just kill, then the killed stand up and kill again. It's a horror... I need help, I need to find the exit but I don't know where.

rldregora.frozen.the_log.title=The Log
rldregora.frozen.the_log.author=Maurice
rldregora.frozen.the_log.lore=The captain's logbook
rldregora.frozen.the_log.page.1=Day 1 - Departure, cargo hold contained fabric, coal and survival supplies such as food and tools which we are meant to deliver to a northern expedition group.\n\nDay 36 - Strange creatures were seen in the waters below, they seemed to cause...
rldregora.frozen.the_log.page.2=severe pain in the head but this was short lived.\n\nDay 84 – Weather is starting to become colder indicating we're getting closer to our destination.\n\nDay 135 - Some of the food supplies have gone missing...\n 
rldregora.frozen.the_log.page.3=and our tender has been stolen. None of the crew members are missing. Maybe we had a stowaway on our ship.\n\nDay 136 – The first mate, a officer and 3 more of the crew went missing. Morale is low but we sailed on.\n 
rldregora.frozen.the_log.page.4=Day 247 – We have arrived at our destination, the camp was abandoned. We will stay the night and return to homeland tomorrow.

rldregora.frozen.survival_basics.title=Survival Basics
rldregora.frozen.survival_basics.author=Unknown
rldregora.frozen.survival_basics.lore=As you open the book a letter falls out.
rldregora.frozen.survival_basics.page.1=You've stepped on death doors, abandon all hope for those who venture without a direct means to return. White sharp clawed monsters roam the tundra's, neither they are your friend neither they are your enemy but behold what is beyond over the fiery canyons that
rldregora.frozen.survival_basics.page.2=split the ice as true monster reign over these lands with fiery breath and floating bodies. Below the ground you may go to the comforts of the forbidden forests which lie beyond the icy glaciers but there the true horrors lurk. May you find the luck of having a ship to 
rldregora.frozen.survival_basics.page.3=return with as ours was eaten by the mighty forces of nature, enveloped by ice and dread as we were forced to abandon our vessel and sacrificed many to these threats. 

##################################################################
# lore/gemtraderswamp.json
##################################################################
rldregora.gemtraderswamp.letter.title=Letter
rldregora.gemtraderswamp.letter.author=Damian
rldregora.gemtraderswamp.letter.lore=This seems to be a smuggler's note.
rldregora.gemtraderswamp.letter.page.1=Quinn, It's safe.\n\nI stashed it nearby the only thing you need to do is get it before it rusts or gets damaged.\n\nIt's in the regular spot. This will be our last job.\n\nDo not try to contact me again,
rldregora.gemtraderswamp.letter.page.2=Be aware there is something prowling down there.\n\nIt reeks of rot.\n\nI hope you red the whole letter instead of letting your greed take over again.\n\nDamian.\n 

##################################################################
# lore/generic.json
##################################################################
rldregora.generic.the_blight1.title=The Blight - Chapter 1
rldregora.generic.the_blight1.author=Dregorian
rldregora.generic.the_blight1.lore=From before the world was named Dregora, the ancient times.
rldregora.generic.the_blight1.page.1=§l§4     Chapter 1  §r\n\nThe year is 2116 and the world is at peace, not because we took a better path, as there are daily riots and looting, but because the nations' fuel reserves reached a point where they could no longer fuel the war machines. This was the
rldregora.generic.the_blight1.page.2=moment where the world leaders came together to initiate Project Arcturus. The goal was to solve the global energy shortage by extracting zero point energy from our own universe, a source of power potentially dozens of times more potent
rldregora.generic.the_blight1.page.3=than a Zero Point Module. However, the project suffered from a fatal flaw. By extracting zero point energy from its own space-time it resulted in the destabilizing of space within the vicinity of the zero point reactor. No longer obeying the
rldregora.generic.the_blight1.page.4=normal laws of physics, exotic particles were formed. They interacted in ways impossible to predict resulting in a runaway reaction in the containment chamber...\n\n 
rldregora.generic.the_blight1.page.5=Without a lot of information to go on, people came to the conclusion space-time had been bent and dimensions had melted together causing the effects of this catastrophe. First the electromagnetic shock wave, powerful enough to destroy the
rldregora.generic.the_blight1.page.6=infrastructure as we knew it. Ships dead in the water, planes with complete system failures and earthquakes destroying our means of transportation on the ground. Months later, just as humanity started to find a grip, the mutations came.
rldregora.generic.the_blight1.page.7=They were called The Corrupted. It started with a few but they quickly became a common occurrence from which even the inhabitants buried deep underground in their mighty concrete bunkers were not safe. Driven back to our last standing
rldregora.generic.the_blight1.page.8=strongholds, we foresaw the future with grim eyes. Far away, behind the horde our advanced nuclear saviors of old times stood, slowly ticking away our remaining time as there was nobody left to fix any damage.  Before long we retreated
rldregora.generic.the_blight1.page.9=to our deepest bunkers, ironically powered by nuclear reactors, and waited for the world to heal again.\n\n 
rldregora.generic.the_blight1.page.10=Meanwhile, a distant hope was approaching this broken, nuclear world, one that would earn the world's name and its history as if they where twins. The Dregorian Voyager, a mighty ship with but one goal, colonize distant stars. A dream
rldregora.generic.the_blight1.page.11=shattered by a simple malfunction within the hyperdrive mainframe that required the passengers to live a thousand years in stasis until they finally arrived back at Earth.\n\n- To be continued in -\n 'lThe Dregorian's Demise'r\n    ( Chapter 2 )

rldregora.generic.dregorian_demise.title=Dregorian's Demise - Chapter 2
rldregora.generic.dregorian_demise.author=Dregorian
rldregora.generic.dregorian_demise.lore=A Distant Hope...
rldregora.generic.dregorian_demise.page.1=§l§4     Chapter 2  §r\\\\n\nAs the staff crew launched into orbit on board a much smaller vessel towards the Dregorian Voyager, all of humanity applauded them. A decade would pass until they would return with what everyone hoped to be good news about one
rldregora.generic.dregorian_demise.page.2=or more distant planets suitable to host human life. A place where they could prosper without the atmosphere being polluted beyond saving. However, among all these good hopes and wishes there was a tiny little object they did not anticipate. Far
rldregora.generic.dregorian_demise.page.3=away, light years in fact, an asteroid was traveling for many million years headed on a collision course with a much larger asteroid. With a chaotic collision they merged, but not completely, as tiny rocks flew off in all
rldregora.generic.dregorian_demise.page.4=directions. One of them headed towards a little moon orbiting a far, far away planet in an unknown system which was currently being visited by the Dregorian Voyager.\n  
rldregora.generic.dregorian_demise.page.5=Nothing special happened, a tiny rock flew at near the speed of light and hit the hull, leaving a tiny hissing gap which was immediately fixed by the autonomous robots with the task to keep the ship in sublime condition. But it was not just the hull
rldregora.generic.dregorian_demise.page.6=that got penetrated. By mere chance this tiny rock meant the death of two crew members. As it was moving so fast it could penetrate anything within the ship, as it did the navigational unit of the hyperdrive mainframe. A senior
rldregora.generic.dregorian_demise.page.7=mechanic could have quickly fixed it, but the longer this chip was not working the more the Dregorian Voyager would drift off towards unknown space.\n 
rldregora.generic.dregorian_demise.page.8=Many years later the Dregorian Voyager reached its destination, or so the crew thought. But after waking they quickly realized something was wrong. Two of the designated mechanics were dead, hit by a tiny rock while in stasis. A tragedy
rldregora.generic.dregorian_demise.page.9=they thought, until they took a look outside and everything was not as it should have been. Unknown stars and planets. Nothing they could recognize from their extended training. Nothing the computer could recognize in its current state as the 
rldregora.generic.dregorian_demise.page.10=shutdown sequence was interrupted by a malfunction in the navigational chip. To sum things up, the hyperdrive would primarily need two replacements, a navigational chip and a new Crontonium Crystal which unintentionally functioned as a fuse
rldregora.generic.dregorian_demise.page.11=and got hit by a surge caused by skipping the shutdown sequence. The navigational chip replacement was nothing to worry about, the same goes for the Crontonium Crystal if it wasn't a one of a kind crystal. Of course there were
rldregora.generic.dregorian_demise.page.12=replacements, but not as good as the initial one.\n\n\nA couple days passed, systems were running again and they knew exactly where they were. In sublime condition their\n\n 
rldregora.generic.dregorian_demise.page.13=destination would have been 5 years ahead. A simple dream away in stasis. Yet the ship could only travel at a mere fraction of its former speed. If the Dregorian Voyager set course for its original destination it would take 987 years to reach while earth was close to a
rldregora.generic.dregorian_demise.page.14=1000 years away. With both destinations nearly equally as bad they voted to return home.\n\n- To be continued in -\n 'lThe Arrival's Demise'r\n    ( Chapter 3 )

rldregora.generic.the_arrival.title=The Arrival - Chapter 3
rldregora.generic.the_arrival.author=Dregorian
rldregora.generic.the_arrival.lore=Red, like the evening sun.
rldregora.generic.the_arrival.page.1=§l§4     Chapter 3  §r\n\nYears passed while the crew of the Dregorian voyager slept in stasis. As the Dregorian Voyager approached the solar system the crew was awakened to make long-distance contact with Earth which seemed so blue the last time they saw it,
rldregora.generic.the_arrival.page.2=around 800 years ago when they left their home. However, upon looking towards the Earth they saw nothing but a planet covered in red dust. Has Earth vanished, somehow replaced by a red ball of dust like Mars? Uncertain of their findings
rldregora.generic.the_arrival.page.3=they tried all methods of contact longing for any answer. Weeks passed while hope declined. Earth as they knew it was gone. Only a small speck of vegetation remained, somehow spared by whatever happened on earth. And so, with mixed
rldregora.generic.the_arrival.page.4=feelings they went to their stasis pods once again to sleep for the remaining 20 years as they slowly approached Earth.\n\n   
rldregora.generic.the_arrival.page.5=20 years passed in a second. Vomiting and feeling incredibly sick, the crew's captain stumbled out of his pod and dragged himself to the infirmary to climb back into another pod and activate it. A day passed while the pod healed him from his
rldregora.generic.the_arrival.page.6=extended hibernation while his other crew members woke up as well. As was second nature, once capable everyone started checking all systems and did a full ship diagnostic. Everything worked fine, including the substitute Crontonium Crystal. As\n 
rldregora.generic.the_arrival.page.7=the crew arrived on deck they could see the captain standing in the center of the room. Behind him there was a red ball, almost like an eye as there was a green iris looking in their direction. What they saw is what remained of Earth. So it was 
rldregora.generic.the_arrival.page.8=\ntrue, the world as they knew it was forever gone, buried under a thick layer of red dust.\n\n- To be continued in -\n§l    A Dead World§r\n    ( Chapter 4 )

rldregora.generic.dead_world.title=A Dead World - Chapter 4
rldregora.generic.dead_world.author=Dregorian
rldregora.generic.dead_world.lore=The sound of nothing as the true king of what once was our Earth.
rldregora.generic.dead_world.page.1=§l§4     Chapter 4  §r\n\nAs the corrupted burned to a crisp, the landing gears of the Dregorian Voyager touched the ground after a thousand years. This was also the moment we woke the scientist department to assess the damage and see what could be done
rldregora.generic.dead_world.page.2=while a small team of marines will attempt to find any survivors to tell us what happened to the Earth. Not much later, the scientists came with a report urging us to visit a known mountain range due north and take some specimens.
rldregora.generic.dead_world.page.3=What we didn't tell them is that we'd not only assemble a team to get the specimens but also visit a special bunker in those mountains. If humanity needed a refuge from an apocalyptic event, that is where they would go.\n 
rldregora.generic.dead_world.page.4=Only one person returned from this expedition with a sample of the mountain. His last words struck the crew with fear and had they not listened I wouldn't be here to tell this story. 'Beasts, corrupted... Evil. Close the gates, NOW! You MUST' As the   
rldregora.generic.dead_world.page.5=scientist did their test we closed up the ship. No one out, no one in. And as night fell we heard the noises against the hull. Dawn arrived as the wind blew over a desolate wasteland and a scientist found the truth. Today marks the year 6156,
rldregora.generic.dead_world.page.6=4076 years since the departure of the Dregorian Voyager. Knowing this and the fact that finding any survivors is very slim, the leaders of the departments came together to talk about the future. Would they remain on Earth and use terraforming 
rldregora.generic.dead_world.page.7=equipment to slowly return the Earth to its former beauty or would they embark on their journey to distant stars as was the original plan? As the vote resulted in a unanimous decision to remain on Earth, they started up the 
rldregora.generic.dead_world.page.8=\n\nzero-point module, their primary source of energy on the Dregorian Voyager.\n\n\n- To be continued in -\n§l    A New World§r\n    ( Chapter 5 )

rldregora.generic.new_world.title=A New World - Chapter 5
rldregora.generic.new_world.author=Dregorian
rldregora.generic.new_world.lore=Welcome to Dregora
rldregora.generic.new_world.page.1=§l§4     Chapter 5  §r\n\nGenerations passed as the land slowly became fertile again. Seeds were spread and trees were popping out of the ground. First there was a river, later came life in the form of forests, animals and birds. The passengers of the
rldregora.generic.new_world.page.2=Dregorian Voyager woke up to this new world. Being told this actually was Earth, they were pained but their will to live was greater than their despair. A huge enclosing wall was constructed to keep out the corrupted so we could sleep in our houses at
rldregora.generic.new_world.page.3=night instead of within the ship. This was also the time of exploration, to see what happened to the world, so towns were created further and further away from the Dregorian Voyager, which slowly but surely began to sink into the ground 
rldregora.generic.new_world.page.4=until nothing remained and an era had passed.\n\nThis is the new world in which we prosper, we the descendants of the Dregorians who once flew among the stars.   
rldregora.generic.new_world.page.5=\n\n\n\n  Welcome to Dregora\n\n§l§4     THE END AND       THE BEGINNING

