rldregora.harbor.secrets_ocean.title=Secrets of the Ocean
rldregora.harbor.secrets_ocean.author=A Traveler
rldregora.harbor.secrets_ocean.lore=Signed by The Traveler
rldregora.harbor.secrets_ocean.page.1=Beneath the ocean waves many secrets await discovery: ancient ships rumored to travel to the stars and beyond, ancient temples with treasures and perhaps the true history of Dregora. I have visited some of these places, found some of
rldregora.harbor.secrets_ocean.page.2=these ancient sunken ruins and gained great wealth by discovering hidden treasures while learning the secret knowledge of the old ways. The old ways which, by the way, were forbidden long ago by the Redcloaks which till this day still exist and
rldregora.harbor.secrets_ocean.page.3=possibly control this world from behind the scenes. I will continue to learn and crack the formula to live 10 lifetimes, like the Redcloaks have done for centuries. Because, unless I am wrong, we are about to enter a time that may change everything.
rldregora.harbor.secrets_ocean.page.4=This is the day I will leave this note, and this trusted village in which I grew up, to find more clues and direct the future towards the best possible outcome.\n\n  

rldregora.harbor.pirates.title=Pirates!
rldregora.harbor.pirates.author=Unknown
rldregora.harbor.pirates.lore=At night they came
rldregora.harbor.pirates.page.1=In the dark night of the eleventh night we hear waves hitting the shore, we hear the docks crumbling under the pressure brought by many evil beings, something not as bad as the corrupted, yet something that nobody should experience. As
rldregora.harbor.pirates.page.2=cannons fire and houses collapse we try to run to safety. Purposely leaving anything of value behind, as this is what they're after. Yet I carry this ancient sword to protect my family. My children and lovely wife, who they will take away from
rldregora.harbor.pirates.page.3=me for their own enjoyment. As we run we see the exit is blocked, so we hide in the hope they won't find us while the sound of their footsteps grow louder and louder...\n 

rldregora.harbor.let_sail.title=Let us set sail
rldregora.harbor.let_sail.author=Unknown
rldregora.harbor.let_sail.lore=Reclaiming the world.
rldregora.harbor.let_sail.page.1=As we carry box by box we're in a happy mood. Not because the pay is good or because we long to feel the ocean waves carrying the ship to our destination. It's because we carry a greater purpose to the ships. It may just be rocks and wood
rldregora.harbor.let_sail.page.2=but from these supplies we will build mighty cities in the middle of the oceans from which we will set sail to conquer this world once again. So we sing happily as we go and build our future.\n 

rldregora.harbor.corrupted_chapter.title=Corrupted Charter
rldregora.harbor.corrupted_chapter.author=Unknown
rldregora.harbor.corrupted_chapter.lore=Taken by the Red Cloaks.
rldregora.harbor.corrupted_chapter.page.1=We're hiding while they slowly progress door to door. They're from a mighty ship without flags. We sit in the corner of my attic while they drag the residents of this harbor out of their houses. Accompanied by tall creatures wearing red and black
rldregora.harbor.corrupted_chapter.page.2=cloaks. I couldn't move a limb as my neighbors screamed and their children were dragged away from them by savage monsters. By the stinking and rotting corrupted. What in Dregora's name is going on? I wonder what they did to deserve this.
rldregora.harbor.corrupted_chapter.page.3=I see the ship take sail, never to be heard of again.\n\n  

rldregora.harbor.corrupted_chapter.title=Sword of the Deep
rldregora.harbor.corrupted_chapter.author=Unknown
rldregora.harbor.corrupted_chapter.lore=What lies under the waves.
rldregora.harbor.corrupted_chapter.page.1=One day, just like any other, I went fishing. Not like the big shots do it with their fancy nets and fleet of fancy ships. No, simply with a fishing rod, some bait and a lot of patience. It wasn't till early afternoon once I finally sat within my simple boat
rldregora.harbor.corrupted_chapter.page.2=with a bucket of bait. Staring at the ocean, which was surprisingly calm, waiting till I would hook something on my line, I saw a reflection under water so I took a closer look. Deep underwater, impossible to see if it wasn't for the calmness of the
rldregora.harbor.corrupted_chapter.page.3=ocean today, it looked like a piece of metal with guards. A beam? No, that must be a sword. Knowing how much swords can cost I undressed myself and jumped from my boat. Reaching the bottom, I tried to move the sword. Is it me?  
rldregora.harbor.corrupted_chapter.page.4=Am I growing old? I couldn't lift the thing an inch so I went back up to grab a rope. After about half an hour I sat on my boat again with the sword next to me, not as heavy as it seemed before. I could just barely lift the bloody thing.
rldregora.harbor.corrupted_chapter.page.5=I wonder what it will be worth, as it's so heavy I don't think it would be very useful in combat, but we'll see.\n\n 

rldregora.harbor.sword_of_deep.name=Sword of the Deep
rldregora.harbor.sword_of_deep.lore=A heavy, magical sword that packs a punch

