rldregora.hiddenmine.mountains_wealth.title=Mountains of wealth
rldregora.hiddenmine.mountains_wealth.author=Unknown
rldregora.hiddenmine.mountains_wealth.lore=A dusty old book containing drawnings, maps and a few words at the end...
rldregora.hiddenmine.mountains_wealth.page.1=My friend once told me of tall mountains with on top abandoned mineshafts leading to riches deep below where he found diamonds, emerald and precious metals per bulk all ready to be digged up. He dreamt of going back there some day as he grew older and stronger.
rldregora.hiddenmine.mountains_wealth.page.2=Capable of extracting the ores... Just a dream had many told him as those who walked away from the convines of the villages and mining outposts were rarely seen again... As did he himself as he went to look for these treasures. I still hope to see his face once
rldregora.hiddenmine.mountains_wealth.page.3=again but it has been years already... Years after he went and chased dreams.

rldregora.hiddenmine.hidden_tunnels.title=Hidden Tunnels
rldregora.hiddenmine.hidden_tunnels.author=Unknown
rldregora.hiddenmine.hidden_tunnels.lore=Notes on findings within the community, it contains a interesting entry.
rldregora.hiddenmine.hidden_tunnels.page.1=Beyond the convines of our settlement there are tunnels, endless tunnels leading in all directions, sometimes breaking open in huge chasms or fiery pits with rivers of lava but even bigger then that had to be the mysterious construction of rock and metal leading
rldregora.hiddenmine.hidden_tunnels.page.2=down to the abyss. I once followed the countless steps and was met by a strong draft that pulled me towards this huge tunnel going on for miles and miles... A mysterious place indeed

rldregora.hiddenmine.endless_book.title=The Endless Book
rldregora.hiddenmine.endless_book.author=Unknown
rldregora.hiddenmine.endless_book.lore=A book of names on those who got lost in the darkness.
rldregora.hiddenmine.endless_book.page.1=This book pays tribute to those who ventured too deep and were swallowed by beings that lurk, mechanisms which trap and pitfalls that kill.\n\nTo Jonny and Cloé, David and Gerald. To Naomi, Albert, Wilson.... and the list goes on.

rldregora.hiddenmine.book_calamities.title=Book of Calamities
rldregora.hiddenmine.book_calamities.author=Unknown
rldregora.hiddenmine.book_calamities.lore=This old book contains a collection of disasters that befell this community, one of them goes as following;
rldregora.hiddenmine.book_calamities.page.1=Beasts dislodged rocks in the caverns behind us blocking our way back. We managed to escape by running forward catching a glimpse of more beasts lurking in a branching tunnel. Moments later rocks fell down behind us, had we been seconds slower we
rldregora.hiddenmine.book_calamities.page.2=would have been trapped. These beasts are getting more and more aggressive as the weeks pass. It started with sabotaging our equipment left behind in the tunnels, then appearances. People started missing and now this.
rldregora.hiddenmine.book_calamities.page.3=These beings... I wonder where they came from and I have my suspicions... One of them looked like one of the missing persons but deformed.. A lot.

rldregora.hiddenmine.hidden_map.title=The Hidden Map
#rldregora.hiddenmine.hidden_map.author=Librarian
rldregora.hiddenmine.hidden_map.lore=One of the three books needed to find the Hidden Library\nWhere the coordinate of Z is negative X is positive.
rldregora.hiddenmine.hidden_map.page.1=For these lands lie in the abyss of maps unfound and unexplored by many and hidden for even the keenest of eyes beyond this book no traces remain and all attempts finding these lands end in vain for there shall only be a few who will venture beyond the real.
rldregora.hiddenmine.hidden_map.page.2=Thou shall find the books; §l§4Valhalla §rin viking realm and The §l§4Pirate's Treasure§r in ships or tropical harbors afloat.
rldregora.hiddenmine.hidden_map.page.3=For these treasures you would need to look in the unexplored lands for viking tales and the seas in southern ends where the pirates hide and jungle thrives.

##################################################################
# lore/hiddenminewaste.json
##################################################################
rldregora.hiddenminewaste.hidden_library.title=Tale of the Hidden Library
#rldregora.hiddenminewaste.hidden_library.author=Librarian
rldregora.hiddenminewaste.hidden_library.lore=This book describes a treasure trove and more interesting, ways on finding it.
rldregora.hiddenminewaste.hidden_library.page.1=\n§4   ⬟─▚  §1⬟─▚  §2⬟─▚§r\n\nThis book is the map to the three keys required in revealing the hidden library stocked to the brim with rare treasures, diamonds, emerald and magical books.\n\n§4   ⬟─▚  §1⬟─▚  §2⬟─▚
rldregora.hiddenminewaste.hidden_library.page.2=\n§4⬟─▚ ⬟─▚ ⬟─▚ ⬟─▚§r\nFor the first key thou shalt walk the ever changing landscape which make up the wastelands within this realm and among the stories of viking warriors you shall find the book Valhalla.\n§4⬟─▚ ⬟─▚ ⬟─▚ ⬟─▚
rldregora.hiddenminewaste.hidden_library.page.3=\n§2⬟─▚ ⬟─▚ ⬟─▚ ⬟─▚§r\nFor the second key thou shalt walk south towards the land of crawling roots and tribal folks. There between the treasures of pirates you shall find a book called The Pirate's Treasure.\n§2⬟─▚ ⬟─▚ ⬟─▚ ⬟─▚
rldregora.hiddenminewaste.hidden_library.page.4=\n§1⬟─▚ ⬟─▚ ⬟─▚ ⬟─▚§r\nFor the third and last key thou shalt walk west and perhaps a bit east until you meet the autumn mountains with villages and mineshafts deep below in which you shall find a book named The Hidden Map.\n§1⬟─▚ ⬟─▚ ⬟─▚ ⬟─▚

rldregora.hiddenminewaste.monoliths_decay.title=Monoliths of decay
rldregora.hiddenminewaste.monoliths_decay.author=Unknown
rldregora.hiddenminewaste.monoliths_decay.lore=There's a loose page, part of a journal so to seem with a single entry...
rldregora.hiddenminewaste.monoliths_decay.page.1=Beyond the ends of these tunnels, out of exits rarely seen the exists massive stretches of land without ceiling in which monoliths of ancient times tower above the sand, steel and molten stone formed creating these giant rusting skeletons to whom no
rldregora.hiddenminewaste.monoliths_decay.page.2=one dares to venture. These are the lands where the quiet rules. There are no animals, nothing... There's just the visitors and the lurking hosts waching from the shadows.

rldregora.hiddenminewaste.secret_passages.title=Secret Passages
rldregora.hiddenminewaste.secret_passages.author=Unknown
rldregora.hiddenminewaste.secret_passages.lore=As you open the book a page falls out containing a drawing of\nlush lands with a huge entryway leading down...
rldregora.hiddenminewaste.secret_passages.page.1=From and to our village exist tunnels in mass, some leading down and other up to the wastelands above where we find massive skeletons of old towering against the sky in which machines and old metal sometimes moans but mostly the it's the quiet that roams.
rldregora.hiddenminewaste.secret_passages.page.2=Along the stretches of unhospitable land where monsters lurk there are other things which defy both logic as reason alike, for who had build these magnificent structures, deep underground far away from the highest clouds where no light shines. These are no
rldregora.hiddenminewaste.secret_passages.page.3=tunnels of ours but more like the skeletons of past. These tunnels lead back and forth to magnificent lands where the arrows point will be the biggest stretch but rewarded you shall be for at the end paradise is what you will meet.

rldregora.hiddenminewaste.lairs_corrupted.title=Lairs of the Corrupted
rldregora.hiddenminewaste.lairs_corrupted.author=Unknown
rldregora.hiddenminewaste.lairs_corrupted.lore=This book contains a warning on dangerous lands.
rldregora.hiddenminewaste.lairs_corrupted.page.1=Despair thou shalt be for when the skies turn black, the horizon turns purple or green poison fills the skies as this is the place where monsters lurk in the depths of the land where blood flows and breeds evil unlike anyone has ever seen.
rldregora.hiddenminewaste.lairs_corrupted.page.2=Despair for this is the land of the wicked from which few return. Despair for when the fog turns heavy and grey as this is the land of the flesh in which thou shalt be food for those that roam underneath in the belly of the earth.

rldregora.hiddenminewaste.beyond_wastelands.title=Beyond the Wastelands
rldregora.hiddenminewaste.beyond_wastelands.author=Unknown
rldregora.hiddenminewaste.beyond_wastelands.lore=The book nearly crumbles in your hands and contains old writing,\nyou can make out a few sentences...
rldregora.hiddenminewaste.beyond_wastelands.page.1=Lava streams below in the canyon, bridges passing over.\n\nAnd there we witnessed a land so beautiful.\n\nLush Jungle unlike our previous expidition to the west.\n 
rldregora.hiddenminewaste.beyond_wastelands.page.2=Saw huge mountains with autumn trees, forests and lakes.\n\nWaterfalls, magnificent.\n\nPeople live here, tribes. In west there were huge settlements.\n\nSettlements with mighty walls.
rldregora.hiddenminewaste.beyond_wastelands.page.3=Voyage back through underground tunnels.\n\nDays of walking. Lots of days.\n\nBeasts and mysterious people clad in black and red roaming around.
rldregora.hiddenminewaste.beyond_wastelands.page.4=Black and Red figured following us, shaked them in the tunnels.\n\nArrived back safely.\n 

##################################################################
# lore/junglebeach.json
##################################################################
rldregora.junglebeach.green_eyes.title=Her green eyes
rldregora.junglebeach.green_eyes.author=Unknown Villager
rldregora.junglebeach.green_eyes.lore=A story written by a previous or current resident.
rldregora.junglebeach.green_eyes.page.1=Silently I stood, looking at what I would carry with me till the end of time. Light breaking through the roof of leaves that served many purposes.\nOne of which  is to protect it's roots from drowning and secondly to quench it's thirst.
rldregora.junglebeach.green_eyes.page.2=That day it however had yet another purpose as it stood witness to a beautiful yet horrific sight.\n\nSurrounded by silence and within that silence the cries of a baby lama being born or parrots looking for a partner.
rldregora.junglebeach.green_eyes.page.3=A cycle of life which both has a start as it has a end.\nBeautiful as she laid between the flowers and grass that wore the same colors as her eyes. Eyes that were beautiful but corrupted as the legends says.\n\nIt's the Grok that wears green eyes.

rldregora.junglebeach.trial_grok.title=Trial of Grok
rldregora.junglebeach.trial_grok.author=Nameless Exile
rldregora.junglebeach.trial_grok.lore=A story on how one experiences the trial of Grok.
rldregora.junglebeach.trial_grok.page.1=It's been the second moon in my trial of Grok and I can slowly feel my senses coming back to me. If not what I wrote would have been gibberish. Or has it been the third moon?\nI think i lost track of time 4 moons ago. But i am getting my sense of time back.
rldregora.junglebeach.trial_grok.page.2=The urge to eat raw fish diminishes too. Cooked are how I like them now.\n\nWith some moons I might be able to return home, back to my family and maybe we can sail out on the ships that will build the new world to the west.
rldregora.junglebeach.trial_grok.page.3=City of origins is what they are going to call it... Weirdly a stranger visited me 9 moons ago. He said it was already created.\n\n\n\nHow long have I been here?\n\n 

rldregora.junglebeach.rawr_way.title=Rawr is the way!
rldregora.junglebeach.rawr_way.author=Loegi Khun
rldregora.junglebeach.rawr_way.lore=This book seems to have been written by a special person...
rldregora.junglebeach.rawr_way.page.1=Hello book! they told me to write, write much about all the raw meat that is so delicious. And easy too! Who needs a cooking pot? Raw legs, raw fish raw heads... Hmm.\n 
rldregora.junglebeach.rawr_way.page.2=I don't understand those idiots back in the village and I am glad they send me away.\n\nMuch better like this anyway! Now, where is my precious rawwrr fishy meat? Yum!

rldregora.junglebeach.book_grok.title=Book of Grok
rldregora.junglebeach.book_grok.author=Village Chief
rldregora.junglebeach.book_grok.lore=A book to guide those who undergo the trial of Grok.
rldregora.junglebeach.book_grok.page.1=If you find yourself in this house you should not leave.\n\nIf you find yourself not alone in this house you should be cautious as corruption may reside here.
rldregora.junglebeach.book_grok.page.2=You should eat cooked fish or meat during evenings. Good will come to those who wont eat raw.\n\nYou should not return to where you came from or you will be pieced by arrows and be set ablaze.
rldregora.junglebeach.book_grok.page.3=You should conquer the GROK and never give up as your family awaits you.

rldregora.junglebeach.noted_encyclopedia.title=Noted Encyclopedia
rldregora.junglebeach.noted_encyclopedia.author=Rediem Lougu
rldregora.junglebeach.noted_encyclopedia.lore=A Dusty, blank book which title says Encyclopedia,\nthere's also a note written on the first two pages.
rldregora.junglebeach.noted_encyclopedia.page.1=Having been here 11 moons I know to have conquered the GROK. On my journeys to regain the light that reside in all of us I found this book deep below. I do not know what it means, what story it tells but it's illustrations and mighty words helped me through my journey.
rldregora.junglebeach.noted_encyclopedia.page.2=Even though I can't seem to read them anymore, perhaps because I have been healed... They were a sight to behold though. Almost as if they were memories from a different age.

